SIMPLE: detoxification
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: detoxification
<hw>detoxification</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a medically
supervised treatment for addiction to drugs or alcohol intended to rid
the body of the addictive substances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>treatment for poisoning by counteracting its toxic
properties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>conversion (of a poisonous substance) to a non-toxic
or harmless state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Detract</ent>⟦br⟧
